window.JIRON_POSTS = [{"slug":"a-simple-insurance-quote-could-save-you-money","title":"A Simple Insurance Quote Could Save You Money","date":"May 24, 2026","ts":"2026-05-24T22:11:32+00:00","img":"assets/blog/img/a-simple-insurance-quote-could-save-you-money.jpg","cat":["Savings","Ahorros"],"excerpt":"When was the last time you reviewed your insurance coverage? Many people stay with the same policy year after year without realizing they could be paying more than necessary. At Feliciano Ji","content":"<p>When was the last time you reviewed your insurance coverage? Many people stay with the same policy year after year without realizing they could be paying more than necessary. At <a href=\"contact.html\">Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency</a>, we make it easy to compare options and find coverage that fits your needs and budget.</p>\n<h2><strong>Why Get a Quote?</strong></h2>\n<p>Insurance rates can change frequently based on factors such as your driving history, home value, location, and even discounts you may qualify for. Taking just a few minutes to get a quote could help you:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Lower your monthly insurance costs</li>\n<li>Find better coverage for the same price</li>\n<li>Bundle multiple policies for additional savings</li>\n<li>Ensure your current coverage still meets your needs</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Whether you're shopping for insurance for the first time or simply want to see if you can save money, our team is here to help.</p>\n<h2><strong>Insurance Solutions for Every Stage of Life</strong></h2>\n<p>At Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency, we can help you find competitive rates on a variety of insurance products, including:</p>\n<h3><strong>Auto Insurance</strong></h3>\n<p>Protect yourself and your vehicle with coverage options designed to fit your budget and lifestyle.</p>\n<h3><strong>Home Insurance</strong></h3>\n<p>Your home is one of your biggest investments. We can help you find coverage that protects what matters most.</p>\n<h3><strong>Renters Insurance</strong></h3>\n<p>Renting a home or apartment? Renters insurance provides affordable protection for your personal belongings and liability coverage.</p>\n<h3><strong>Life Insurance</strong></h3>\n<p>Give your loved ones financial security and peace of mind with life insurance coverage tailored to your family's needs.</p>\n<h3><strong>Boat Insurance</strong></h3>\n<p>Enjoy your time on the water knowing your boat and equipment are protected.</p>\n<h3><strong>Business Insurance</strong></h3>\n<p>From small businesses to growing companies, we can help protect your business with customized insurance solutions.</p>\n<h2><strong>Refer a Friend and Earn $20</strong></h2>\n<p>We appreciate our customers and believe that referrals are the highest compliment we can receive. That's why we offer a simple referral program.</p>\n<p>When you refer a friend, family member, coworker, or neighbor to <a href=\"contact.html\">Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency</a> and they receive a quote, you'll earn <strong>$20</strong> as our way of saying thank you.</p>\n<p>It's easy:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Refer someone to our agency.</li>\n<li>They contact us for a quote.</li>\n<li>You earn $20 for your referral.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>There’s no limit to helping friends explore their insurance options while earning rewards along the way.</p>\n<h2><strong>Ready to See How Much You Could Save?</strong></h2>\n<p>Don't assume you're getting the best rate available. A quick insurance quote could uncover savings and provide better protection for your family, home, vehicle, business, or recreational vehicles.</p>\n<p>Contact <a href=\"contact.html\">Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency</a> today at <a href=\"tel:7025220079\">(702)522-0079</a> to get a free quote and learn how much you could save. While you're at it, refer a friend and earn $20 for helping them find the coverage they need.</p>"},{"slug":"why-college-students-need-renters-insurance","title":"Why College Students Need Renters Insurance","date":"May 20, 2026","ts":"2026-05-20T15:55:04+00:00","img":"assets/blog/img/why-college-students-need-renters-insurance.png","cat":["Renters","Inquilinos"],"excerpt":"If you’re getting ready to move into your first apartment, dorm, or shared house, renters insurance may not be the first thing on your mind. Most students are focused on classes, decorating ","content":"<p>If you’re getting ready to move into your first apartment, dorm, or shared house, renters insurance may not be the first thing on your mind. Most students are focused on classes, decorating their new place, and figuring out how to survive on ramen noodles. But renters insurance can protect the things you’ve worked hard for, without costing a fortune.</p>\n<p>Many college students are surprised to learn that a landlord’s insurance policy does <strong>not</strong> cover personal belongings. If your laptop gets stolen, your apartment floods, or a fire damages your furniture and clothes, you could be responsible for replacing everything out of pocket.</p>\n<p>That’s where renters insurance comes in.</p>\n<h2><strong>What Does Renters Insurance Cover?</strong></h2>\n<p>A renters insurance policy can help protect things like:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Laptops and electronics</li>\n<li>Furniture and clothing</li>\n<li>Textbooks and school supplies</li>\n<li>Gaming systems and TVs</li>\n<li>Bikes and personal belongings</li>\n</ul>\n<p>It can also provide liability protection if someone gets injured in your apartment and may even help cover temporary living expenses if your rental becomes unlivable after a covered loss.</p>\n<h2><strong>Affordable Coverage for Students</strong></h2>\n<p>One of the biggest misconceptions about renters insurance is that it’s expensive. In reality, renters insurance is one of the most affordable insurance policies available.</p>\n<p>According to recent reports, many college students pay around $15–$25 per month for coverage, and some policies can cost even less depending on the coverage selected.</p>\n<p>That’s often less than the cost of a few coffee runs each month, and much cheaper than replacing a stolen laptop or damaged furniture.</p>\n<h2><strong>Why It Matters for College Students</strong></h2>\n<p>College students often own more valuable items than they realize. Between phones, tablets, laptops, headphones, gaming systems, and clothes, the cost to replace everything can add up quickly.</p>\n<p>In fact, nearly all college students surveyed who had renters insurance said they found it beneficial, with many saying the low cost and peace of mind made it worth it.</p>\n<p>Whether you’re living off-campus with roommates or moving into your very first apartment, renters insurance helps protect you from unexpected situations that could otherwise become major financial setbacks.</p>\n<h2><strong>Tips for Saving Money on Renters Insurance</strong></h2>\n<p>Here are a few ways students can keep coverage affordable:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Choose only the coverage you need</li>\n<li>Bundle renters and auto insurance policies</li>\n<li>Ask about student discounts</li>\n<li>Install basic safety devices like smoke detectors or deadbolts</li>\n<li>Compare deductible options</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>Protect Your Future While Staying on Budget</strong></h2>\n<p>Starting college comes with enough stress already. Renters insurance gives students and parents peace of mind knowing personal belongings have protection if the unexpected happens.</p>\n<p>At <a href=\"contact.html\">Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency</a>, we help college students find affordable renters insurance that fits their budget and lifestyle. Whether you’re moving into a dorm, apartment, or shared house, our team can help you explore simple, low-cost coverage options designed to protect what matters most.</p>\n<p>Call or Text us today at <a href=\"tel:7025220079\">(702)522-0079</a> for a quick renters insurance quote and move into your new place with confidence.</p>"},{"slug":"protecting-your-las-vegas-home-this-summer","title":"Protecting Your Las Vegas Home This Summer","date":"May 11, 2026","ts":"2026-05-11T01:55:41+00:00","img":"assets/blog/img/protecting-your-las-vegas-home-this-summer.png","cat":["Home","Hogar"],"excerpt":"Summer in Las Vegas means sunshine, pool days, and triple-digit temperatures, but it can also bring unique risks for homeowners. From extreme heat to monsoon storms, taking a few preventativ","content":"<p>Summer in Las Vegas means sunshine, pool days, and triple-digit temperatures, but it can also bring unique risks for homeowners. From extreme heat to monsoon storms, taking a few preventative steps now can help protect your home, save money, and avoid costly insurance claims later.</p>\n<h2><strong>Prepare for Extreme Heat</strong></h2>\n<p>Las Vegas summers are no joke. Prolonged heat can put stress on your roof, air conditioning system, and even plumbing. Make sure your AC is serviced before temperatures peak, replace air filters regularly, and inspect your roof for cracked tiles or signs of wear.</p>\n<p>It’s also a good idea to check weather stripping around doors and windows to help keep cool air inside and energy bills lower.</p>\n<h2><strong>Be Ready for Monsoon Season</strong></h2>\n<p>Summer storms in Southern Nevada can arrive quickly with strong winds, heavy rain, and flash flooding. Clean out gutters and drains to prevent water buildup, and trim any trees or branches that could fall during high winds.</p>\n<p>If you live in an area prone to flooding, review your insurance coverage to understand what is and isn’t covered before storm season begins.</p>\n<h2><strong>Protect Your Home While Traveling</strong></h2>\n<p>Many families travel during the summer months, making homes more vulnerable to theft. Consider installing smart security cameras, motion lights, or a monitored alarm system. Ask a trusted neighbor to collect packages or check on your property while you’re away.</p>\n<p>Simple steps like putting lights on timers and holding mail delivery can also make your home appear occupied.</p>\n<h2><strong>Reduce Fire Risks</strong></h2>\n<p>Outdoor grills, dry landscaping, and extreme heat can increase fire hazards during the summer. Keep grills away from structures, avoid storing flammable items in garages exposed to heat, and clear dry brush or debris around your property.</p>\n<p>Checking smoke detectors and replacing batteries is another quick but important safety measure.</p>\n<h2><strong>Review Your Insurance Coverage</strong></h2>\n<p>Summer is a great time to review your homeowners insurance policy and make sure your coverage still fits your needs. Home upgrades, new valuables, or rising repair costs may mean it’s time for an update. <a href=\"contact.html\">Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency</a> can help you!</p>\n<p>Having the right protection in place can give you peace of mind all season long.</p>\n<p>Stay safe, stay cool, and enjoy everything summer in Las Vegas has to offer!</p>\n<p>Call or Text us today at (<a href=\"tel:7025220079\">702)522-0079</a>!</p>"},{"slug":"earn-20-just-for-helping-a-friend-stay-protected","title":"Earn $20 Just for Helping a Friend Stay Protected","date":"May 4, 2026","ts":"2026-05-04T01:32:47+00:00","img":"assets/blog/img/earn-20-just-for-helping-a-friend-stay-protected.png","cat":["Savings","Ahorros"],"excerpt":"When it comes to insurance, most people don’t think about it until they really need it. That’s why having a trusted local agency on your side matters, and that’s exactly what you’ll find at ","content":"<p>When it comes to insurance, most people don’t think about it until they really need it. That’s why having a trusted local agency on your side matters, and that’s exactly what you’ll find at <a href=\"index.html\">Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency</a>.</p>\n<p>Known for their personalized service and straightforward approach, the team at Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency helps clients find the right coverage without the confusion. Whether it’s auto, home, renters, business, or life insurance, they take the time to walk you through your options so you can feel confident in your decisions.</p>\n<h2><strong>Introducing Their New $20 Referral Program</strong></h2>\n<p>Now, they’re giving back to their community in a simple (and rewarding) way.</p>\n<p>With their new referral program, you can earn <strong>$20 just for referring a friend</strong> to the agency. It’s that easy:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Tell a friend or family member about Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency</li>\n<li>When they get a quote or become a client</li>\n<li>You receive <strong>$20 as a thank-you</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>No complicated steps. No hidden requirements. Just a straightforward way to get rewarded for helping someone you know find better insurance.</p>\n<h2><strong>Why Refer Your Friends?</strong></h2>\n<p>Referring someone isn’t just about earning $20, it’s about helping them get the coverage they actually need.</p>\n<p>The agency is known for:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Taking a personalized approach to every client</li>\n<li>Explaining coverage in a way that’s easy to understand</li>\n<li>Offering multiple insurance options to fit different budgets and needs</li>\n</ul>\n<p>So when you refer a friend, you’re not just sending them anywhere—you’re connecting them with a team that genuinely cares.</p>\n<h2><strong>A Win-Win for Everyone</strong></h2>\n<p>At the end of the day, this referral program is a win for everyone:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>You</strong> get rewarded with $20</li>\n<li><strong>Your friend</strong> gets help finding the right insurance</li>\n<li><strong>The agency</strong> continues to grow through trusted recommendations</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you already trust <a href=\"index.html\">Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency</a>, this is a great opportunity to share that experience, and get something back in return. Call or Text Us Today at <a href=\"tel:7025220079\">(702)522-0079</a>.</p>"},{"slug":"what-insurance-does-a-small-business-need-a-complete-guide-for-business-owners","title":"What Insurance Does a Small Business Need? A Complete Guide for Business Owners","date":"April 13, 2026","ts":"2026-04-13T01:33:14+00:00","img":"assets/blog/img/what-insurance-does-a-small-business-need-a-complete-guide-for-business-owners.png","cat":["Business","Negocio"],"excerpt":"Starting and running a small business is exciting, but it also comes with risks. From unexpected accidents to legal claims, even a single incident can have a major financial impact. That’s w","content":"<h2><strong>What Insurance Does a Small Business Need? A Complete Guide for Business Owners</strong></h2>\n<p>Starting and running a small business is exciting, but it also comes with risks. From unexpected accidents to legal claims, even a single incident can have a major financial impact. That’s why having the right insurance coverage isn’t just smart, it’s essential.</p>\n<p>At Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency, we help small business owners find the right protection tailored to their unique needs. Here’s a breakdown of the most important types of insurance every small business should consider.</p>\n<h3><strong>1. General Liability Insurance</strong></h3>\n<p>This is the foundation of most business insurance plans. General liability insurance protects your business from claims involving:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bodily injury (like a customer slipping in your store)</li>\n<li>Property damage</li>\n<li>Personal or advertising injury (such as defamation)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Without it, you could be responsible for legal fees, medical costs, and settlements out of pocket.</p>\n<h3><strong>2. Professional Liability Insurance (Errors &amp; Omissions)</strong></h3>\n<p>If your business provides services or advice, this coverage is crucial. It protects against claims of:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Negligence</li>\n<li>Mistakes</li>\n<li>Failure to deliver services as promised</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Even if you didn’t do anything wrong, legal defense costs alone can be expensive.</p>\n<h3><strong>3. Commercial Property Insurance</strong></h3>\n<p>Whether you own or lease your space, this insurance covers damage to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Buildings</li>\n<li>Equipment</li>\n<li>Inventory</li>\n<li>Furniture</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Events like fires, theft, or natural disasters can disrupt your business. This coverage helps you recover quickly.</p>\n<h3><strong>4. Workers’ Compensation Insurance</strong></h3>\n<p>If you have employees, most states require this coverage. It provides:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Medical benefits for work-related injuries</li>\n<li>Wage replacement for injured employees</li>\n<li>Protection for employers against lawsuits</li>\n</ul>\n<p>It’s not just a legal requirement, it shows your team you value their safety.</p>\n<h3><strong>5. Business Owner’s Policy (BOP)</strong></h3>\n<p>A Business Owner’s Policy bundles key coverages (typically general liability and commercial property) into one cost-effective package. It’s a great option for small to mid-sized businesses looking for comprehensive protection at a lower price.</p>\n<h3><strong>6. Commercial Auto Insurance</strong></h3>\n<p>If your business uses vehicles for operations, personal auto policies won’t cover business-related incidents. Commercial auto insurance protects against:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Accidents</li>\n<li>Vehicle damage</li>\n<li>Liability claims</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>7. Cyber Liability Insurance</strong></h3>\n<p>In today’s digital world, even small businesses are targets for cyberattacks. This coverage helps with:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Data breaches</li>\n<li>Customer notification costs</li>\n<li>Legal fees</li>\n<li>Reputation management</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you store customer information, this is increasingly important.</p>\n<h3><strong>8. Business Interruption Insurance</strong></h3>\n<p>What happens if your business has to temporarily close due to a disaster? Business interruption insurance helps cover:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Lost income</li>\n<li>Operating expenses</li>\n<li>Rent and payroll</li>\n</ul>\n<p>It can be the difference between reopening and shutting down permanently.</p>\n<h2><strong>Every Business Is Different. Your Coverage Should Be Too.</strong></h2>\n<p>There’s no one-size-fits-all insurance plan. The type of coverage you need depends on your industry, size, location, and risk level.</p>\n<p>That’s where Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency comes in. As a broker, we work with multiple insurance providers to find you the best coverage at the most competitive price, so you can focus on growing your business with confidence.</p>\n<p><strong>Protect Your Business Today!</strong>Don’t wait until something goes wrong to think about insurance. The right coverage gives you peace of mind and a solid foundation for success.</p>\n<p><strong>Contact <a href=\"contact.html\">Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency</a> today</strong> to explore your options and build a policy that fits your business needs. Call or Text us today at <a href=\"tel:7025220079\">(702)522-0079</a>.</p>"},{"slug":"feliciano-jiron-insurance-agency-sponsors-local-athlete-xy-whitney","title":"Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency Sponsors Local Athlete Xy Whitney","date":"April 5, 2026","ts":"2026-04-05T19:38:48+00:00","img":"assets/blog/img/feliciano-jiron-insurance-agency-sponsors-local-athlete-xy-whitney.jpg","cat":["Community","Comunidad"],"excerpt":"At Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency, community support goes beyond policies. It’s about investing in people, dreams, and the spirit of Las Vegas. That’s why we’re proud to sponsor Xy Whitney","content":"<p>At <a href=\"contact.html\">Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency</a>, community support goes beyond policies. It’s about investing in people, dreams, and the spirit of Las Vegas. That’s why we’re proud to sponsor Xy Whitney, a dedicated athlete and inspiring local figure who is making waves both on and off the field.</p>\n<p>Xy Whitney is not only a member of the <a href=\"https://www.lvsilverstars.com/\">Las Vegas Silver Stars</a>, but also a student, a mom, and a full-contact football player. In addition to all of this, she is a board-certified health coach working full time, further showcasing her commitment to helping others live healthier, stronger lives.</p>\n<p>Her journey is a powerful example of determination, resilience, and balance. All qualities that resonate deeply with our values as a local business.</p>\n<p>After signing with the Silver Stars in early January, Xy officially began her rookie season, stepping into a challenging and competitive environment with confidence and drive. Full-contact women’s football demands strength, discipline, and commitment, and Xy embodies all three. Whether she’s on the field pushing her limits, coaching clients toward better health, in the classroom working toward her goals, or at home caring for her family, she continues to show what it truly means to pursue your passions relentlessly.</p>\n<p>At <a href=\"contact.html\">Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency</a>, we believe in uplifting individuals who make a difference in our community. Sponsoring Xy is more than just supporting an athlete, it’s about recognizing a role model who inspires others to chase their dreams, no matter how demanding life may be.</p>\n<p>We are honored to be part of Xy Whitney’s journey and look forward to cheering her on throughout her rookie season and beyond. Her story is a reminder that strength comes in many forms, and here in Las Vegas, it’s stronger than ever.</p>"},{"slug":"a-guide-to-mobile-home-insurance-in-nevada","title":"A Guide to Mobile Home Insurance in Nevada","date":"March 22, 2026","ts":"2026-03-22T17:47:18+00:00","img":"assets/blog/img/a-guide-to-mobile-home-insurance-in-nevada.png","cat":["Home","Hogar"],"excerpt":"Owning a mobile home in Nevada offers flexibility, affordability, and a place to truly call your own. But just like a traditional home, your mobile home deserves the right protection. At Fel","content":"<p>Owning a mobile home in Nevada offers flexibility, affordability, and a place to truly call your own. But just like a traditional home, your mobile home deserves the right protection. At <a href=\"contact.html\">Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency</a>, we help Nevada residents find reliable, affordable mobile home insurance that brings peace of mind, no matter what life throws your way.</p>\n<h2><strong>What Is Mobile Home Insurance?</strong></h2>\n<p>Mobile home insurance is designed specifically to protect manufactured and mobile homes. It typically covers your home’s structure, personal belongings, and liability in case someone is injured on your property. Whether your home is in a park or on private land, having the right coverage is essential.</p>\n<h2><strong>Why Mobile Home Insurance Matters in Nevada</strong></h2>\n<p>Living in Nevada comes with unique risks, from strong desert winds and extreme heat to unexpected fires and storms. Without proper insurance, even a small incident can turn into a major financial burden.</p>\n<p>Mobile home insurance helps you:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Protect your home from damage caused by fire, wind, and other covered events</li>\n<li>Replace or repair personal belongings</li>\n<li>Cover liability costs if someone is injured on your property</li>\n<li>Afford temporary housing if your home becomes unlivable</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>What Does a Policy Typically Cover?</strong></h2>\n<p>A standard mobile home insurance policy may include:</p>\n<p><strong>Dwelling Coverage</strong> Protects the structure of your mobile home, including attached features like awnings or porches.</p>\n<p><strong>Personal Property Coverage</strong> Helps replace belongings like furniture, electronics, and clothing if they’re damaged or stolen.</p>\n<p><strong>Liability Protection</strong> Covers legal and medical expenses if someone is injured on your property.</p>\n<p><strong>Additional Living Expenses (ALE)</strong> Pays for temporary housing and living costs if your home is damaged and you need to relocate.</p>\n<h2><strong>How to Know If You Have Enough Coverage</strong></h2>\n<p>Many homeowners underestimate the value of their belongings or the cost to fully rebuild their home. It’s important to review your policy regularly and make sure it reflects:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Current home value</li>\n<li>Upgraded features or additions</li>\n<li>The true value of your personal belongings</li>\n</ul>\n<p>At <a href=\"contact.html\">Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency</a>, we take the time to walk you through your options and ensure your coverage fits your needs, not just your budget.</p>\n<h2><strong>Save Money with Discounts</strong></h2>\n<p>We believe protecting your home shouldn’t break the bank. That’s why we help our clients find available discounts, such as:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bundling home and auto insurance</li>\n<li>Installing safety features like smoke detectors or security systems</li>\n<li>Being claim-free</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>Why Choose <a href=\"contact.html\">Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency</a>?</strong></h2>\n<p>We’re more than just an insurance provider, we’re part of the community. Our team is dedicated to helping Nevada families protect what matters most with personalized service and honest guidance.</p>\n<p>When you work with us, you get:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Local expertise and personalized recommendations</li>\n<li>Access to multiple insurance carriers for the best rates</li>\n<li>Friendly, bilingual support</li>\n<li>Ongoing policy reviews to keep your coverage up to date</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>Get Started Today</strong></h2>\n<p>Your mobile home is more than just a place to live, it’s where memories are made. Don’t leave it unprotected. Contact <a href=\"contact.html\">Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency</a> today to get a customized mobile home insurance quote and make sure you’re covered for whatever comes next. Call or Text us today at <a href=\"tel:7025220079\">(702)522-0079</a>!</p>"},{"slug":"notary-services-at-feliciano-jiron-insurance-agency","title":"Notary Services at Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency","date":"March 22, 2026","ts":"2026-03-22T16:53:42+00:00","img":"assets/blog/img/notary-services-at-feliciano-jiron-insurance-agency.png","cat":["Community","Comunidad"],"excerpt":"When it comes to handling important documents, having access to a reliable notary can make all the difference. At Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency, we’re proud to offer professional, afforda","content":"<p>When it comes to handling important documents, having access to a reliable notary can make all the difference. At <a href=\"contact.html\">Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency</a>, we’re proud to offer professional, affordable notary services designed to make your life easier, all in one convenient location.</p>\n<h2><strong>Why Choose Our Notary Services?</strong></h2>\n<p>As a trusted insurance provider in Las Vegas, our agency is built on providing dependable, personalized service to our community. In addition to helping clients protect what matters most through insurance, we also offer notary services to support your everyday needs.</p>\n<p>Whether you're signing legal documents, verifying identity, or completing official paperwork, our team ensures a smooth and efficient experience.</p>\n<h2><strong>Notary Services We Offer</strong></h2>\n<p>We provide a wide range of notary services at competitive rates:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Acknowledgments</strong> $15 for the first signature\n   $7.50 for each additional signature</li>\n<li><strong>Oaths or Affirmations</strong> $7.50 per individual (without signature)</li>\n<li><strong>Jurats</strong> $15 per signature</li>\n<li><strong>Certified Copies</strong> $7.50 per certificate</li>\n<li><strong>Marriage Ceremonies</strong> $75</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Our goal is to keep pricing transparent and affordable, so you know exactly what to expect before your appointment.</p>\n<h2><strong>Exclusive Benefit for Our Clients</strong></h2>\n<p>One of the biggest perks of working with Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency is that <strong>notary services are completely free for our policyholders</strong>. It’s just one of the many ways we go above and beyond to provide value to our clients.</p>\n<h2><strong>More Than Just Insurance</strong></h2>\n<p>At our agency, we believe in being a one-stop resource for our community. From auto and home insurance to notary services, we are committed to making essential services accessible, convenient, and stress-free.</p>\n<h2><strong>Visit Us Today</strong></h2>\n<p>If you need a document notarized, skip the hassle of searching for a notary and visit <a href=\"contact.html\">Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency</a>. Our friendly, knowledgeable team is here to help you every step of the way. Call or Text us today at <a href=\"tel:7025220079\">(702)522-0079!</a></p>"},{"slug":"unlock-savings-at-every-turn-55-driver-discounts-with-feliciano-jiron-insurance-agency","title":"Unlock Savings at Every Turn: 55+ Driver Discounts with Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency","date":"March 2, 2026","ts":"2026-03-02T00:08:12+00:00","img":"assets/blog/img/unlock-savings-at-every-turn-55-driver-discounts-with-feliciano-jiron-insurance-agency.png","cat":["Savings","Ahorros"],"excerpt":"As we get older, we gain experience, wisdom… and sometimes higher auto insurance premiums. But here’s the good news: if you’re 55 years or older, you could be eligible for meaningful discoun","content":"<p>As we get older, we gain experience, wisdom… and sometimes higher auto insurance premiums. But here’s the good news: if you’re <strong>55 years or older</strong>, you could be eligible for meaningful discounts on your auto insurance, and working with an experienced local team like <a href=\"contact.html\">Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency</a> can help you make the most of them.</p>\n<h2><strong>Who Is Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency?</strong></h2>\n<p><a href=\"contact.html\">Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency</a> is a trusted independent insurance agency based in Las Vegas, NV. They help drivers of all ages find the right coverage from auto and home policies to life, renters, and business protection, with personalized service and guidance. Their team speaks both English and Español, making insurance accessible to a wider community.</p>\n<p><a href=\"contact.html\">Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency</a> offers a wide range of discount opportunities designed to help drivers save on their auto insurance premiums. As an independent agency working with multiple reputable carriers, they can identify and apply the best available discounts for each individual’s unique profile. This includes savings for mature or 55+ drivers who complete approved safety courses. Their experienced team takes the time to review your current coverage, explain all available savings options, and tailor a policy that maximizes value without compromising protection, making it easier and more affordable for customers to get the coverage they need.</p>\n<h2><strong>Why Are 55+ Discounts Available?</strong></h2>\n<p>Insurers recognize that many drivers aged 55 and better have:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>A long track record of driving experience</li>\n<li>Lower annual mileage</li>\n<li>A commitment to staying safe on the road</li>\n</ul>\n<p>As a result, many carriers offer discounts to this age group, especially when drivers take steps to refresh their driving knowledge or maintain a clean driving record.</p>\n<h2><strong>Common 55+ Driver Discount Opportunities</strong></h2>\n<p>Here are some of the most common ways mature drivers can save on car insurance:</p>\n<h3><strong>Mature Driver / Defensive Driving Discounts</strong></h3>\n<p>Many states offer discounted premiums if you complete a state-approved mature driver or defensive driving course. For example, drivers 55+ who complete an approved course can receive a discount that typically lasts for three years.</p>\n<p>These courses often cover:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Safe driving techniques</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Updates to traffic laws</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Age-related challenges behind the wheel</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Good Driving Record</strong></p>\n<p>If you’ve kept a clean driving record with no accidents or violations, many insurers will offer additional savings, sometimes stacking alongside other mature-driver discounts.</p>\n<h3><strong>Bundling Policies</strong></h3>\n<p>Insuring your auto and home (or renters) with the same company often leads to a <strong>multi-policy discount</strong>, giving you even more value for your insurance dollar.</p>\n<h2><strong>How Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency Can Help</strong></h2>\n<p>Because the team at <a href=\"contact.html\">Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency</a> works with multiple insurance carriers, they can:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Compare quotes</strong> to identify the most competitive rates</li>\n<li><strong>Explain which discounts you qualify for</strong> as a driver 55 or older</li>\n<li><strong>Help schedule approved driver safety courses</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Handle paperwork and follow-up with insurers</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Insurance isn’t just about buying a policy, it’s about understanding how to optimize coverage and savings. An independent agent is one of your best allies in that process.</p>\n<h2><strong>Final Tips for Mature Drivers</strong></h2>\n<p>Ask your agent specifically about:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Mature driver / defensive driving discounts</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Low-mileage discounts</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Loyalty or long-time customer discounts</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Multi-vehicle and multi-policy discounts</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Working with a friendly and knowledgeable team like <a href=\"contact.html\">Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency</a> ensures you’re not leaving money on the table. Call or text them today at <a href=\"tel:7025220079\">(702)522-0079</a>!</p>"},{"slug":"is-your-home-insurance-enough-heres-how-to-know","title":"Is Your Home Insurance Enough? Here’s How to Know","date":"February 16, 2026","ts":"2026-02-16T23:47:46+00:00","img":"assets/blog/img/is-your-home-insurance-enough-heres-how-to-know.png","cat":["Home","Hogar"],"excerpt":"Living in Nevada comes with a lot of perks such as sunshine, growth, beautiful desert landscapes, and booming communities. But it also comes with unique risks that can impact whether your ho","content":"<p>Living in Nevada comes with a lot of perks such as sunshine, growth, beautiful desert landscapes, and booming communities. But it also comes with unique risks that can impact whether your home insurance is truly enough.</p>\n<p>With rising construction costs across the state and increased wildfire exposure in many areas, many Nevada homeowners are unknowingly underinsured.</p>\n<p>Here’s how to make sure your coverage actually protects your home and everything inside it.</p>\n<h2><strong>1. Does Your Coverage Reflect Nevada’s Current Rebuild Costs?</strong></h2>\n<p>Your dwelling coverage should reflect the <strong>cost to rebuild your home in Nevada today.</strong> Not what you paid for it and not its current market value.</p>\n<p>Across cities like Las Vegas, Reno, and Henderson, construction costs have risen due to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Labor shortages</li>\n<li>Increased material costs</li>\n<li>Population growth</li>\n<li>Updated building codes</li>\n</ul>\n<p>After regional wildfires or wind events, rebuilding costs can spike even higher due to demand.</p>\n<h3><strong>Ask Yourself:</strong></h3>\n<p>If your home were a total loss tomorrow, would your policy rebuild it exactly as it stands today?</p>\n<p>If you’re unsure, your dwelling limit likely needs a review.</p>\n<h2><strong>2. Are You Protected Against Nevada Wildfire Risk?</strong></h2>\n<p>Wildfire risk has increased across parts of Nevada, especially in Northern Nevada and areas near open desert land.</p>\n<p>Standard homeowners insurance typically covers fire damage but:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Are your limits high enough?</li>\n<li>Do you have extended replacement cost coverage?</li>\n<li>Has your insurer updated your risk rating recently?</li>\n</ul>\n<p>In wildfire-prone areas, underinsurance can become financially devastating if rebuild costs surge after a major event.</p>\n<h2><strong>3. Do You Have Enough Coverage for Everything Inside Your Home?</strong></h2>\n<p>Most Nevada policies automatically include personal property coverage, often 50–70% of your dwelling limit.</p>\n<p>But think about everything inside your home:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Furniture</li>\n<li>Electronics</li>\n<li>Clothing</li>\n<li>Appliances</li>\n<li>Jewelry</li>\n<li>Tools</li>\n<li>Outdoor equipment</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Replacing everything at once after a fire or major loss is far more expensive than most homeowners realize.</p>\n<h3><strong>Pro Tip:</strong></h3>\n<p>Do a video walkthrough of your home. Open drawers and closets. Document high-value items.</p>\n<p>Also check for special limits on:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Jewelry</li>\n<li>Firearms</li>\n<li>Collectibles</li>\n<li>Business equipment (if you work from home)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Many of these items require additional endorsements to be fully covered.</p>\n<h2><strong>4. Replacement Cost vs. Actual Cash Value (This Matters More Than You Think)</strong></h2>\n<p>Some policies in Nevada still include <strong>Actual Cash Value</strong> coverage for personal property, meaning depreciation is deducted.</p>\n<p><strong>Example:</strong>\nA 6-year-old couch that cost $2,000 may only pay out a few hundred dollars after depreciation.</p>\n<p><strong>You want:</strong>\nReplacement Cost on the dwelling\nReplacement Cost on personal property</p>\n<p>Without it, you could pay significantly out of pocket after a claim.</p>\n<h2><strong>5. Flood Coverage: A Major Nevada Misconception</strong></h2>\n<p>Many Nevada homeowners assume flooding isn’t a concern because we live in the desert.</p>\n<p>But Nevada experiences:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Flash floods</li>\n<li>Monsoon storms</li>\n<li>Sudden heavy rainfall</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Standard homeowners insurance does <strong>not</strong> cover flood damage.</p>\n<p>If your property is in a flood-prone area, especially in parts of Las Vegas or low-lying desert communities, you may need a separate flood policy.</p>\n<h2><strong>6. Is Your Liability Coverage High Enough?</strong></h2>\n<p>Nevada is a growing state with increasing property values. If someone is injured on your property, liability coverage protects you from lawsuits and medical expenses.</p>\n<p>Most policies start at $100,000.</p>\n<p>Many professionals recommend at least $300,000–$500,000 especially if you have:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>A pool</li>\n<li>Pets</li>\n<li>Rental properties</li>\n<li>Frequent guests</li>\n</ul>\n<p>An umbrella policy can provide additional protection at a relatively low cost.</p>\n<h2><strong>Signs You Might Be Underinsured in Nevada</strong></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Your policy hasn’t been reviewed in 2+ years</li>\n<li>You’ve renovated or upgraded your home</li>\n<li>You purchased high-value electronics or jewelry</li>\n<li>Construction costs in your area have risen</li>\n<li>You’re unsure what your rebuild cost actually is</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>The Bottom Line for Nevada Homeowners</strong></h2>\n<p>Home insurance isn’t about checking a box, it’s about financial protection.</p>\n<p>With rising rebuild costs, wildfire exposure, and flash flood risks, Nevada homeowners should review their coverage annually to make sure it truly reflects today’s risks and replacement values.</p>\n<p>A quick review today could prevent a financial disaster tomorrow.</p>\n<p>Call or Text <a href=\"contact.html\">Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency</a> at <a href=\"tel:7025220079\">(702)522-0079</a> to talk to a Licenced Insurance Agent about your Home Coverage!</p>"},{"slug":"what-is-full-coverage-a-simple-explaination-for-drivers","title":"What Is Full Coverage? A Simple Explaination for Drivers","date":"February 9, 2026","ts":"2026-02-09T03:18:50+00:00","img":"assets/blog/img/what-is-full-coverage-a-simple-explaination-for-drivers.png","cat":["Auto","Auto"],"excerpt":"If you’ve ever shopped for car insurance, you’ve probably heard the term “full coverage.” It sounds reassuring, but what does it actually mean?","content":"<p>If you’ve ever shopped for car insurance, you’ve probably heard the term <strong>“full coverage.”</strong> It sounds reassuring, but what does it actually mean?</p>\n<p>Here’s a simple, no-confusion explanation so you can decide what coverage is right for you.</p>\n<h2><strong>The Short Answer: “Full Coverage” Isn’t a Real Policy</strong></h2>\n<p>Surprisingly, <strong>full coverage isn’t an official insurance term.</strong> It usually refers to a <strong>combination of coverages</strong> that protect both <strong>you, your car, and others</strong> in most common driving situations.</p>\n<p>Think of it as a bundle, not a guarantee that everything is covered.</p>\n<h2><strong>What People Usually Mean by Full Coverage</strong></h2>\n<p>When drivers say “full coverage,” they’re typically referring to these three main parts:</p>\n<h3><strong>1. Liability Coverage (Required in Most States)</strong></h3>\n<p>This pays for <strong>damage or injuries you cause to others</strong> in an accident.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Covers other people’s medical bills</li>\n<li>Covers damage to their vehicle or property</li>\n<li><strong>Does not cover your own car</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>This is the minimum coverage most states require.</p>\n<h3><strong>2. Collision Coverage</strong></h3>\n<p>This helps pay to repair or replace <strong>your car</strong> if you’re in an accident, regardless of who’s at fault.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Hitting another car</li>\n<li>Hitting an object (like a pole or guardrail)</li>\n<li>Single-car accidents</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you’re still paying off your vehicle, lenders usually require this.</p>\n<h3><strong>3. Comprehensive Coverage</strong></h3>\n<p>This covers damage to your car from <strong>non-collision events</strong>, such as:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Theft</li>\n<li>Fire</li>\n<li>Vandalism</li>\n<li>Storms, hail, floods</li>\n<li>Hitting an animal</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Together, <strong>liability + collision + comprehensive</strong> is what most people mean by “full coverage.”</p>\n<h2><strong>What Full Coverage Does</strong> <strong>Not</strong> <strong>Automatically Include</strong></h2>\n<p>Even with full coverage, some things may still require add-ons:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Rental car coverage</li>\n<li>Roadside assistance</li>\n<li>Gap insurance</li>\n<li>Medical payments or personal injury protection</li>\n<li>Coverage for custom parts or upgrades</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Always review your policy so there are no surprises.</p>\n<h2><strong>Do You Need Full Coverage?</strong></h2>\n<p><strong>Full coverage is often a good idea if:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Your car is newer or worth a lot</li>\n<li>You’re financing or leasing your vehicle</li>\n<li>You couldn’t afford to replace your car out of pocket</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>You might consider dropping parts of full coverage if:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Your car is older and paid off</li>\n<li>The cost of coverage is more than the car’s value</li>\n<li>You have savings to handle repairs or replacement</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>Final Thoughts</strong></h2>\n<p>“Full coverage” doesn’t mean <strong>everything is covered</strong>, but it does mean <strong>broader protection and peace of mind</strong>. The key is understanding what’s included and what isn’t, so you can choose coverage that fits your life and budget.</p>\n<p>If you’re unsure what coverage you currently have or what you should carry, talking with a licensed insurance agent at <a href=\"contact.html\">Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency</a> can help you make a confident decision.</p>\n<p>Call or text us today at <a href=\"tel:7025220079\">(702)522-0079</a>!</p>"},{"slug":"why-roof-maintenance-matters-for-home-insurance","title":"Why Roof Maintenance Matters for Home Insurance","date":"February 9, 2026","ts":"2026-02-09T03:01:44+00:00","img":"assets/blog/img/why-roof-maintenance-matters-for-home-insurance.png","cat":["Home","Hogar"],"excerpt":"When it comes to protecting your home, your roof is your first line of defense, especially in the Southwest. In states like Nevada, Arizona, and New Mexico, extreme weather, intense sun, and","content":"<p>When it comes to protecting your home, your roof is your first line of defense, especially in the Southwest. In states like <strong>Nevada, Arizona, and New Mexico</strong>, extreme weather, intense sun, and seasonal storms can take a serious toll on roofing systems. What many homeowners don’t realize is that <strong>roof condition plays a major role in insurance coverage, claims approval, and even premium costs</strong>.</p>\n<h2><strong>The Unique Climate Challenges of the Southwest</strong></h2>\n<p>Homes in Nevada, Arizona, and New Mexico face environmental stressors that aren’t as common in other parts of the country:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Intense UV exposure</strong> that breaks down roofing materials faster</li>\n<li><strong>Extreme heat</strong> causing shingles to crack, curl, or deteriorate</li>\n<li><strong>Monsoon storms</strong> bringing heavy rain, high winds, and hail</li>\n<li><strong>Dust and debris</strong> that clog drainage systems and trap moisture</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Over time, these conditions can weaken your roof, even if there are no obvious signs from the ground.</p>\n<h2><strong>Why Insurance Companies Care About Roof Maintenance</strong></h2>\n<p>From an insurance perspective, a poorly maintained roof is considered a <strong>preventable risk</strong>. Most homeowners insurance policies require you to maintain your property in good condition. If a claim is filed and the damage is traced back to neglect, insurers may:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Deny or partially deny claims</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Reduce payout amounts</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Increase premiums</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Require roof replacement to continue coverage</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Non-renew the policy altogether</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>For example, water damage caused by long-term roof deterioration may not be covered, even if the damage becomes severe.</p>\n<h2><strong>Common Roof Issues Insurers Look For</strong></h2>\n<p>Insurance companies often assess roof condition during underwriting, renewal, or after a claim.</p>\n<p>Some red flags include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Missing, cracked, or curling shingles</li>\n<li>Soft spots or sagging areas</li>\n<li>Evidence of leaks or water staining</li>\n<li>Roofs nearing or exceeding their expected lifespan</li>\n<li>Improper or outdated roofing materials</li>\n</ul>\n<p>In states like Arizona and Nevada, many insurers are especially strict about <strong>roof age</strong>, sometimes limiting coverage once a roof reaches 15–20 years old, depending on the material.</p>\n<h2><strong>How Regular Roof Maintenance Protects Your Coverage</strong></h2>\n<p>Routine roof maintenance isn’t just good homeownership, it’s a smart insurance strategy.</p>\n<p>Benefits include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Lower risk of denied claims</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Improved eligibility with more carriers</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Potential premium savings</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Faster claims processing</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Extended roof lifespan</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Simple steps like annual inspections, clearing debris, repairing minor damage quickly, and documenting maintenance can make a major difference.</p>\n<h2><strong>Documentation Matters More Than You Think</strong></h2>\n<p>Keeping records of roof inspections, repairs, and replacements can help tremendously if you ever file a claim. Insurers are far more likely to approve claims when homeowners can show they took reasonable steps to maintain the property.</p>\n<p>Tip: Save invoices, inspection reports, photos, and warranties in a digital folder for easy access.</p>\n<h2><strong>Protect Your Roof, Protect Your Policy</strong></h2>\n<p>In the Southwest, roof maintenance isn’t optional, it’s essential. Whether you’re dealing with scorching desert heat in Arizona, high winds in New Mexico, or sudden storms in Nevada, staying ahead of roof issues can protect both your home <strong>and</strong> your insurance coverage.</p>\n<p>If you’re unsure how your roof condition affects your policy, speaking with a knowledgeable insurance agent at <a href=\"contact.html\">Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency</a> can help you avoid surprises and ensure you’re properly protected.</p>\n<p>Give us a call today to find the insurance that meets your needs! Call or text us at <a href=\"tel:7025220079\">(702)522-0079</a>.</p>"},{"slug":"term-vs-whole-life-insurance-whats-better-for-your-family","title":"Term vs. Whole Life Insurance: What’s Better for Your Family?","date":"February 2, 2026","ts":"2026-02-02T01:11:37+00:00","img":"assets/blog/img/term-vs-whole-life-insurance-whats-better-for-your-family.png","cat":["Life","Vida"],"excerpt":"When you’re protecting your family’s future, life insurance isn’t just another financial product, it’s peace of mind. But one of the most common questions families ask is: Should we choose t","content":"<p>When you’re protecting your family’s future, life insurance isn’t just another financial product, it’s peace of mind. But one of the most common questions families ask is: <strong>Should we choose term life or whole life insurance?</strong></p>\n<p>The short answer? It depends on your family’s needs, budget, and long-term goals. Let’s break it down in simple terms so you can make a confident decision.</p>\n<h2><strong>What Is Term Life Insurance?</strong></h2>\n<p><strong>Term life insurance</strong> provides coverage for a specific period of time (typically 10, 20, or 30 years). If you pass away during that term, your beneficiaries receive a payout (death benefit). If the term ends and you’re still living, coverage expires unless you renew or convert it.</p>\n<h3><strong>Why Families Choose Term Life</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Lower monthly cost</strong> (often much more affordable)</li>\n<li><strong>High coverage amounts</strong> for income replacement</li>\n<li>Ideal for <strong>young families</strong>, new homeowners, or parents with kids</li>\n<li>Covers critical years like mortgages, childcare, and education costs</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Things to Keep in Mind</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Coverage is <strong>temporary</strong></li>\n<li>No cash value or savings component</li>\n<li>Premiums can increase if you renew later in life</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Best for: Families who want strong protection during their highest-expense years.</p>\n<h2><strong>What Is Whole Life Insurance?</strong></h2>\n<p><strong>Whole life insurance</strong> lasts your entire lifetime as long as premiums are paid. It includes a <strong>cash value component</strong> that grows over time and can be borrowed against.</p>\n<h3><strong>Why Families Choose Whole Life</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Lifetime coverage</strong></li>\n<li>Fixed premiums that never increase</li>\n<li>Builds cash value you can use later</li>\n<li>Can help with <strong>estate planning</strong> or leaving a guaranteed legacy</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Things to Keep in Mind</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Significantly higher premiums</strong></li>\n<li>Cash value grows slowly in early years</li>\n<li>Not always necessary for short-term protection needs</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Best for: Families focused on long-term planning, wealth transfer, or final expenses.</p>\n<h2><strong>So… Which Is Better for Your Family?</strong></h2>\n<p>For <strong>most families</strong>, especially those with young children, <strong>term life insurance is often the better starting point</strong>. It provides maximum protection at an affordable cost when your family needs it most.</p>\n<p>However, <strong>whole life insurance</strong> can make sense if:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You’ve already secured term coverage</li>\n<li>You want lifelong protection</li>\n<li>You’re planning for inheritance or final expenses</li>\n<li>Your budget allows for higher premiums</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Many families choose a combination</strong>- term life for income protection and a smaller whole life policy for long-term security.</p>\n<h2><strong>Final Thoughts</strong></h2>\n<p>There’s no one-size-fits-all answer when it comes to life insurance. The best policy is the one that fits your family’s <strong>current needs</strong>, <strong>future goals</strong>, and <strong>budget</strong>.</p>\n<p>If you’re unsure which option makes sense for you, a licensed insurance professional at <a href=\"contact.html\">Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency</a> can help you compare policies and build a plan that grows with your family. Call or text us today at <a href=\"tel:7025220079\">(702)522-0079</a>!</p>\n<p>Your family deserves protection and clarity!</p>"},{"slug":"insurance-bundle-discounts-how-combining-policies-can-save-you-up-to-30","title":"Insurance Bundle Discounts: How Combining Policies Can Save You Up to 30%","date":"January 26, 2026","ts":"2026-01-26T05:07:15+00:00","img":"assets/blog/img/insurance-bundle-discounts-how-combining-policies-can-save-you-up-to-30.jpg","cat":["Savings","Ahorros"],"excerpt":"When it comes to insurance, many people don’t realize they may be paying more than necessary simply by keeping their policies separate. One of the easiest ways to lower your insurance costs,","content":"<p>When it comes to insurance, many people don’t realize they may be paying more than necessary simply by keeping their policies separate. One of the easiest ways to lower your insurance costs, without reducing coverage, is by bundling multiple policies with the same insurance carrier.</p>\n<p>Insurance bundle discounts reward customers for combining policies such as home, auto, life, and renters insurance. Depending on how much you bundle, savings can range anywhere from <strong>15% to 30% on average</strong>.</p>\n<h3><strong>What Is an Insurance Bundle?</strong></h3>\n<p>An insurance bundle means purchasing more than one type of insurance policy from the same provider. Common bundles include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Home + Auto</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Auto + Renters</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Home + Auto + Life</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Auto + Renters + Life</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>The more policies you bundle, the larger the potential discount. Insurance companies value long-term relationships and lower administrative costs, and they pass those savings on to customers through bundle discounts.</p>\n<h3><strong>How Much Can You Save?</strong></h3>\n<p>On average, bundling insurance policies can save you <strong>between 15% and 30%</strong>, depending on:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The number of policies bundled</li>\n<li>The types of coverage</li>\n<li>Your individual risk factors</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For example, bundling home and auto insurance alone often results in significant savings. Adding renters or life insurance can increase the discount even more, sometimes lowering premiums across multiple policies.</p>\n<h3><strong>Additional Benefits of Bundling</strong></h3>\n<p>Beyond cost savings, bundling offers several practical advantages:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Simplified payments</strong> – Fewer bills to manage</li>\n<li><strong>One point of contact</strong> – Easier communication with your agent or carrier</li>\n<li><strong>Consistent coverage reviews</strong> – Policies can be adjusted together as your life changes</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Is Bundling Right for Everyone?</strong></h3>\n<p>While bundling works well for many people, it’s important to review coverage carefully. The goal isn’t just saving money, it’s ensuring you have the right protection. An insurance professional can compare bundled options against standalone policies to make sure you’re getting both value and adequate coverage.</p>\n<h3><strong>Final Thoughts</strong></h3>\n<p>Insurance bundle discounts are one of the simplest ways to reduce premiums while maintaining strong coverage. Whether you own a home, rent, drive, or want to protect your family with life insurance, bundling policies can lead to meaningful savings and added convenience.</p>\n<p>If you’re curious how much you could save by bundling home, auto, life, or renters insurance, call or text <a href=\"contact.html\">Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency</a> at <a href=\"tel:7025220079\">(702)522-0079</a> to get your quote!</p>"},{"slug":"senior-55-discount-how-drivers-can-save-up-to-15-on-car-insurance","title":"Senior 55+ Discount: How Drivers Can Save Up to 15% on Car Insurance","date":"January 26, 2026","ts":"2026-01-26T04:49:52+00:00","img":"assets/blog/img/senior-55-discount-how-drivers-can-save-up-to-15-on-car-insurance.jpg","cat":["Savings","Ahorros"],"excerpt":"If you’re 55 or older, you may be leaving hundreds of dollars on the table when it comes to car insurance. Many drivers are surprised to learn that completing a simple, affordable driving co","content":"<p>If you’re 55 or older, you may be leaving hundreds of dollars on the table when it comes to car insurance. Many drivers are surprised to learn that completing a simple, affordable driving course can unlock <strong>significant auto insurance savings</strong> without exams, stress, or time pressure.</p>\n<p>Here’s everything you need to know about the <strong>Senior 55+ Auto Insurance Discount</strong> and how it can benefit you.</p>\n<h3><strong>What Is the Senior 55+ Auto Insurance Discount?</strong></h3>\n<p>The Senior 55+ discount is designed specifically for experienced drivers aged 55 and older. By completing a state-approved defensive driving or mature driver course, eligible drivers can save <strong>up to 15% on their car insurance premiums</strong>.</p>\n<p>On average, drivers who qualify save <strong>around $300 per year</strong>, making this one of the easiest ways to reduce insurance costs.</p>\n<h3><strong>States With Guaranteed Discounts</strong></h3>\n<p>Drivers in the following states are <strong>guaranteed eligibility</strong> for the Senior 55+ discount once the course is completed:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Nevada (NV)</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Arizona (AZ)</strong></li>\n<li><strong>New Mexico (NM)</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you live in one of these states, insurance companies are required to apply the discount when you provide your completion certificate.</p>\n<h3><strong>What Does the Course Involve?</strong></h3>\n<p>One of the biggest benefits of this program is how easy and flexible it is.</p>\n<p><strong>Here’s what to expect:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>100% online course</strong> — complete it from home or in our office</li>\n<li><strong>No timed test</strong> — go at your own pace</li>\n<li><strong>No final exam pressure</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Certificate available immediately</strong> upon completion</li>\n<li><strong>Valid for 3 years</strong> — enjoy savings long-term</li>\n<li><strong>Course cost is approximately $30</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>The course focuses on safe driving habits, updated traffic laws, and defensive driving techniques that can make you a safer, more confident driver.</p>\n<h3><strong>Immediate Savings With Minimal Effort</strong></h3>\n<p>For a small one-time course fee, you could save hundreds of dollars each year on your car insurance. Over the three-year validity period, that can add up to <strong>nearly $1,000 in savings</strong>, all without changing your coverage.</p>\n<h3><strong>Need Help? We’re Here for You</strong></h3>\n<p>Not comfortable taking the course alone? No problem.</p>\n<p>We offer:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>In-office course access</strong></li>\n<li><strong>One-on-one tutoring</strong> through the course material</li>\n<li>Step-by-step guidance to ensure you receive your certificate and discount</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Our goal is to make the process simple, stress-free, and worthwhile.</p>\n<h3><strong>Ready to Start Saving?</strong></h3>\n<p>If you’re 55 or older and live in Nevada, Arizona, or New Mexico, this discount is one of the easiest ways to lower your car insurance costs. Reach out to <a href=\"contact.html\">Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency</a> today to get started, ask questions, or schedule help with the course.</p>\n<p>Call or text us today at (<a href=\"tel:7025220079\">702)522-0079</a>!</p>\n<h3><strong>Small effort. Big savings. Peace of mind on the road.</strong></h3>"},{"slug":"common-insurance-myths-that-put-your-small-business-at-risk","title":"Common Insurance Myths That Put Your Small Business at Risk","date":"January 19, 2026","ts":"2026-01-19T07:45:20+00:00","img":"assets/blog/img/common-insurance-myths-that-put-your-small-business-at-risk.png","cat":["Business","Negocio"],"excerpt":"Running a small business comes with enough challenges and insurance shouldn’t be one of them. Unfortunately, many small business owners make decisions based on misunderstandings about how bu","content":"<p>Running a small business comes with enough challenges and insurance shouldn’t be one of them. Unfortunately, many small business owners make decisions based on misunderstandings about how business insurance actually works. These misconceptions can leave businesses underinsured, overpaying, or exposed to serious financial risk.</p>\n<p>Let’s break down the most common insurance myths small businesses believe, and the truth behind them.</p>\n<h3></h3>\n<h3><strong>Misconception #1: “My Business Is Too Small to Need Insurance”</strong></h3>\n<p>Many owners assume insurance is only necessary for large companies with employees, offices, or high revenue. In reality, <strong>small businesses are often more vulnerable</strong> because they don’t have large cash reserves to absorb unexpected losses.</p>\n<p>A single lawsuit, accident, or property loss could financially cripple a small business, even a home-based or side-hustle operation.</p>\n<p><strong>The truth:</strong> If you interact with customers, clients, vendors, or the public in any way, you likely need insurance.</p>\n<h3></h3>\n<h3><strong>Misconception #2: “General Liability Covers Everything”</strong></h3>\n<p>General liability insurance is essential, but it’s not a catch-all policy. It typically covers bodily injury, property damage, and advertising injury but <strong>not</strong> everything a business faces.</p>\n<p><strong>What it usually does NOT cover:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Professional mistakes or negligence</li>\n<li>Employee injuries</li>\n<li>Cyberattacks or data breaches</li>\n<li>Damage to your own equipment or property</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>The truth:</strong> Most businesses need multiple coverages tailored to their risks, not just one policy.</p>\n<h3><strong>Misconception #3: “If I Have an LLC, I Don’t Need Insurance”</strong></h3>\n<p>Forming an LLC or corporation helps protect your personal assets, but it does <strong>not</strong> replace insurance.</p>\n<p>Legal structures protect against certain liabilities, but they don’t prevent:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Lawsuits</li>\n<li>Legal defense costs</li>\n<li>Claims against your business assets</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>The truth:</strong> Insurance and business entities work together, one doesn’t eliminate the need for the other.</p>\n<h3></h3>\n<h3><strong>Misconception #4: “Insurance Is Too Expensive for My Budget”</strong></h3>\n<p>Cost is one of the biggest reasons small businesses delay getting insured. However, many owners are surprised to learn that basic coverage is often far more affordable than expected.</p>\n<p>In many cases, <strong>the cost of insurance is significantly less than the cost of one uncovered claim</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>The truth:</strong> Insurance is an investment in protecting your income, reputation, and future, not just an expense.</p>\n<h3></h3>\n<h3><strong>Misconception #5: “Home Insurance Covers My Business”</strong></h3>\n<p>Homeowners or renters insurance offers very limited, if any, coverage for business activities. Even when some coverage exists, it’s usually capped at low limits and excludes liability related to business operations.</p>\n<p><strong>The truth:</strong> If you run a business from home, you likely need a separate business policy or endorsement to avoid coverage gaps.</p>\n<h3></h3>\n<h3><strong>Misconception #6: “I’ll Get Insurance When My Business Grows”</strong></h3>\n<p>Waiting until your business is “big enough” to get insurance is risky. Accidents, claims, and lawsuits can happen at any stage, especially during early growth when resources are limited.</p>\n<p><strong>The truth:</strong> The earlier you insure your business, the better protected you are during growth and transition periods.</p>\n<h3></h3>\n<h3><strong>Misconception #7: “All Insurance Policies Are Basically the Same”</strong></h3>\n<p>Not all policies are created equal. Coverage limits, exclusions, endorsements, and claims handling can vary widely, even between similar policies.</p>\n<p><strong>The truth:</strong> The cheapest policy isn’t always the best. The right policy is one that fits your specific industry, operations, and risks.</p>\n<h3><strong>Final Thoughts</strong></h3>\n<p>Insurance doesn’t have to be confusing or overwhelming, but misunderstanding it can be costly. By clearing up these common misconceptions, small business owners can make informed decisions that protect what they’ve worked so hard to build.</p>\n<p>If you’re unsure what coverage your business truly needs, speaking with an insurance professional such as <a href=\"contact.html\">Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency</a> can help you avoid gaps, overpaying, and unnecessary risk. Give us a call today at <a href=\"tel:7025220079\">702-522-0079</a> to get a quote on your business!</p>"},{"slug":"the-truth-about-life-insurance-through-work-vs-private-policies","title":"The Truth About Life Insurance Through Work vs. Private Policies","date":"January 19, 2026","ts":"2026-01-19T07:42:47+00:00","img":"assets/blog/img/the-truth-about-life-insurance-through-work-vs-private-policies.png","cat":["Life","Vida"],"excerpt":"Life insurance is one of the most important financial tools you can have to protect your loved ones. But when it comes time to enroll, many people wonder: Is the life insurance offered throu","content":"<p>Life insurance is one of the most important financial tools you can have to protect your loved ones. But when it comes time to enroll, many people wonder: <strong>Is the life insurance offered through work enough?</strong></p>\n<p>While employer-provided life insurance is a great benefit, it’s not always the best, or only solution. Understanding the differences between <strong>life insurance offered through work</strong> and <strong>private life insurance</strong> can help you make a more confident, long-term decision.</p>\n<h3><strong>What Is Life Insurance Through Work?</strong></h3>\n<p>Employer-provided life insurance (also called group life insurance) is coverage offered as part of your employee benefits package.</p>\n<h3><strong>How It Works</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Usually <strong>term life insurance</strong></li>\n<li>Coverage amount is often <strong>1–2 times your annual salary</strong> but can be lower.</li>\n<li>Premiums are <strong>low or free</strong> because they’re subsidized by your employer</li>\n<li>Enrollment is easy, often with <strong>little or no medical underwriting</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Pros of Life Insurance Through Work</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Convenient and automatic enrollment</li>\n<li>Affordable or employer-paid</li>\n<li>No medical exam required in most cases</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Cons of Life Insurance Through Work</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Coverage is often <strong>limited</strong> and may not be enough for your family’s needs</li>\n<li>You typically <strong>lose coverage if you leave your job</strong></li>\n<li>Limited ability to customize beneficiaries, riders, or policy length</li>\n<li>Coverage amounts usually increase in cost as you age</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>What Is Private Life Insurance?</strong></h2>\n<p>Private life insurance is a policy you purchase independently through an insurance agent or company. You own the policy, not your employer.</p>\n<h3><strong>Types of Private Life Insurance</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Term Life Insurance</strong> – coverage for a set number of years (10, 20, 30)</li>\n<li><strong>Whole or Permanent Life Insurance</strong> – lifetime coverage with potential cash value</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Pros of Private Life Insurance</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>You own the policy</strong>, regardless of job changes</li>\n<li>Higher and customizable coverage amounts</li>\n<li>Locked-in rates (especially with term life)</li>\n<li>Ability to add riders (child rider, living benefits, etc.)</li>\n<li>Long-term financial planning flexibility</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Cons of Private Life Insurance</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Requires an application and sometimes a medical exam</li>\n<li>Higher upfront cost compared to group coverage</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Is Life Insurance Through Work Enough?</strong></h3>\n<p>For most families, <strong>employer-provided life insurance alone is not enough</strong>.</p>\n<p>A general rule of thumb is to have <strong>10–15 times your annual income</strong> in life insurance coverage. Employer plans often fall short, especially if you have:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Children or dependents</li>\n<li>A mortgage</li>\n<li>Student loans or other debts</li>\n<li>A spouse who relies on your income</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Should You Have Both?</strong></h3>\n<p>In many cases, <strong>the best strategy is having both</strong>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Use your <strong>employer-provided life insurance</strong> as a supplemental benefit</li>\n<li>Secure a <strong>private policy</strong> for long-term, reliable coverage</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This approach ensures your family stays protected no matter what happens with your job or career.</p>\n<h3><strong>Final Thoughts</strong></h3>\n<p>Life insurance through work is a great starting point—but it shouldn’t be your only plan. A private life insurance policy gives you control, stability, and peace of mind that lasts beyond your employment.</p>\n<p>If you’re unsure how much coverage you need or which option is right for your situation, speaking with a licensed insurance professional at <a href=\"contact.html\">Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency</a> can help you make the best decision for your family’s future. Give us a call at <a href=\"tel:7025220079\">702-522-0079</a>!</p>"},{"slug":"most-common-auto-insurance-claims-in-nevada-and-how-to-avoid-them","title":"Most Common Auto Insurance Claims in Nevada and How to Avoid Them","date":"January 15, 2026","ts":"2026-01-15T05:28:03+00:00","img":"assets/blog/img/most-common-auto-insurance-claims-in-nevada-and-how-to-avoid-them.png","cat":["Auto","Auto"],"excerpt":"Nevada drivers face unique road risks, from heavy tourist traffic to long desert highways and unpredictable weather. As a result, certain auto insurance claims occur far more often than othe","content":"<p>Nevada drivers face unique road risks, from heavy tourist traffic to long desert highways and unpredictable weather. As a result, certain auto insurance claims occur far more often than others. Knowing the most common auto insurance claims in Nevada, and how to avoid them, can help you stay safer on the road and keep your insurance costs under control.</p>\n<h2><strong>1. Rear-End Collisions</strong></h2>\n<p>Rear-end accidents are the most common auto insurance claim in Nevada, especially in congested areas like Las Vegas and Reno. Sudden braking, distracted driving, and tailgating are major contributors.</p>\n<p><strong>How to Avoid It:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Maintain a safe following distance</li>\n<li>Stay alert in stop-and-go traffic</li>\n<li>Avoid phone use while driving</li>\n<li>Anticipate traffic slowdowns early</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>2. Parking Lot Accidents</strong></h2>\n<p>Busy parking lots at casinos, shopping centers, and events lead to frequent low-speed accidents. These claims often involve backing up, tight spaces, or unclear right-of-way.</p>\n<p><strong>How to Avoid It:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Park farther away where traffic is lighter</li>\n<li>Back into parking spaces when possible</li>\n<li>Drive slowly and stay alert for pedestrians</li>\n<li>Use mirrors and backup cameras carefully</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>3. Sideswipe Accidents and Lane-Change Collisions</strong></h2>\n<p>Highway driving and multilane roads contribute to sideswipe accidents, especially when drivers fail to check blind spots or signal properly.</p>\n<p><strong>How to Avoid It:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Always signal before changing lanes</li>\n<li>Check mirrors and blind spots</li>\n<li>Avoid lingering in other drivers’ blind spots</li>\n<li>Be extra cautious during rush hour</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>4. Hit-and-Run Accidents</strong></h2>\n<p>Hit-and-run incidents are unfortunately common in Nevada, particularly in urban and tourist-heavy areas. These claims often require uninsured motorist coverage to resolve.</p>\n<p><strong>How to Avoid It:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Park in well-lit, secure areas</li>\n<li>Install a dash cam</li>\n<li>Carry uninsured motorist coverage</li>\n<li>Document accidents immediately if they occur</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>5. Weather-Related Accidents</strong></h2>\n<p>Although Nevada is known for its dry climate, rain, wind, dust storms, and icy conditions in northern Nevada can cause sudden road hazards.</p>\n<p><strong>How to Avoid It:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Reduce speed during poor weather</li>\n<li>Maintain proper tire tread</li>\n<li>Use headlights in low visibility</li>\n<li>Avoid driving during severe dust storms when possible</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>6. Animal Collisions</strong></h2>\n<p>Rural highways and desert roads increase the risk of hitting wildlife, particularly at night.</p>\n<p><strong>How to Avoid It:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Slow down in posted wildlife zones</li>\n<li>Use high beams when safe to do so</li>\n<li>Stay alert during dawn and dusk</li>\n<li>Avoid swerving abruptly to miss animals</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>Why Avoiding Claims Matters</strong></h2>\n<p>Even minor auto insurance claims can lead to higher premiums over time. While Nevada law requires minimum liability coverage, carrying adequate coverage—such as collision and uninsured motorist protection—can help protect you financially when accidents happen.</p>\n<h2><strong>Final Thoughts</strong></h2>\n<p>Auto accidents can happen to even the safest drivers, but understanding the most common auto insurance claims in Nevada can help you reduce risk and drive more confidently. Defensive driving, proper vehicle maintenance, and the right insurance coverage all play a key role in protecting you on the road.</p>\n<p>Reviewing your auto insurance policy regularly ensures you’re properly covered for Nevada’s driving conditions and helps you avoid costly surprises after an accident.</p>\n<p>If you have an questions please don’t hesitate to call or text <a href=\"contact.html\">Feliciano Jiron Insurance Agency</a> at <a href=\"tel:7025220079\">(702)522-0079</a></p>"},{"slug":"how-insurance-claims-work-from-start-to-finish","title":"How Insurance Claims Work: From Start to Finish","date":"January 15, 2026","ts":"2026-01-15T05:13:52+00:00","img":"assets/blog/img/how-insurance-claims-work-from-start-to-finish.png","cat":["Auto","Auto"],"excerpt":"Filing an insurance claim can feel overwhelming, especially when you’re already dealing with an accident, damage, or unexpected loss. Understanding how the claims process works from start to","content":"<p>Filing an insurance claim can feel overwhelming, especially when you’re already dealing with an accident, damage, or unexpected loss. Understanding how the claims process works from start to finish can help you feel more confident and less stressed when the time comes.</p>\n<p>This guide walks you through each step of an insurance claim, what to expect, and how to avoid common mistakes.</p>\n<h3><strong>Step 1: A Loss or Incident Occurs</strong></h3>\n<p>An insurance claim begins when a covered event happens. This could include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>A car accident</li>\n<li>Damage to your home from fire, theft, or weather</li>\n<li>A medical expense</li>\n<li>Loss or damage to personal property</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Your policy determines what types of incidents are covered, so it’s important to review your coverage ahead of time and not after something goes wrong.</p>\n<h3><strong>Step 2: Review Your Insurance Policy</strong></h3>\n<p>Before filing a claim, take a moment to review your policy and understand:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>What is covered and what isn’t</li>\n<li>Your deductible (the amount you pay out of pocket)</li>\n<li>Coverage limits</li>\n<li>Any deadlines for reporting a claim</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This helps set realistic expectations and prevents surprises later in the process.</p>\n<h3><strong>Step 3: File the Claim</strong></h3>\n<p>You can usually file a claim in one of the following ways:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Online through your insurer’s website or app</li>\n<li>By phone with a claims representative</li>\n<li>Through your insurance agent</li>\n</ul>\n<p>You’ll be asked for basic information, such as:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Date and time of the incident</li>\n<li>What happened</li>\n<li>Photos or documentation (if available)</li>\n<li>Police reports or receipts (if applicable)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Tip: File your claim as soon as possible. Delays can sometimes complicate or slow down the process.</p>\n<h3><strong>Step 4: Claim Is Assigned to an Adjuster</strong></h3>\n<p>Once your claim is submitted, the insurance company assigns a claims adjuster. The adjuster’s job is to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Investigate the claim</li>\n<li>Review documentation</li>\n<li>Determine whether the loss is covered</li>\n<li>Estimate the cost of repairs or replacement</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The adjuster may contact you for additional details, request photos, or schedule an inspection.</p>\n<h3><strong>Step 5: Investigation and Evaluation</strong></h3>\n<p>During this stage, the insurer verifies the facts of the claim. This may include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Inspecting vehicle or property damage</li>\n<li>Reviewing medical records or repair estimates</li>\n<li>Interviewing involved parties</li>\n<li>Confirming coverage under your policy</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This step ensures the claim is accurate and fairly evaluated.</p>\n<h3><strong>Step 6: Claim Decision</strong></h3>\n<p>After the investigation, the insurance company will make a decision to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Approve the claim</strong> (fully or partially)</li>\n<li><strong>Deny the claim</strong> (if it’s not covered or lacks required documentation)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If approved, the insurer will explain:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The settlement amount</li>\n<li>How the payment is calculated</li>\n<li>What costs are covered after your deductible</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If denied, you’ll receive a written explanation outlining why.</p>\n<h3><strong>Step 7: Payment or Repairs</strong></h3>\n<p>Once approved, payment is issued in one of several ways:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Direct payment to you</li>\n<li>Payment to a repair shop, contractor, or medical provider</li>\n<li>A combination of both</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For property or auto claims, repairs may begin once payment is issued or approved.</p>\n<h3><strong>Step 8: Claim Closure</strong></h3>\n<p>After payment is made and repairs are completed, the claim is officially closed. Be sure to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Review all documents and settlement details</li>\n<li>Confirm repairs were completed properly</li>\n<li>Keep claim records for future reference</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If issues arise after closure, you may be able to reopen the claim depending on your policy and situation.</p>\n<h3><strong>Common Mistakes to Avoid When Filing a Claim</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Waiting too long to file</li>\n<li>Not documenting damage with photos or videos</li>\n<li>Admitting fault prematurely</li>\n<li>Failing to understand deductibles and limits</li>\n<li>Not asking questions when something is unclear</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>Final Thoughts</strong></h2>\n<p>Insurance claims don’t have to be intimidating. Knowing how the process works, from the initial incident to final payment, puts you in control and helps ensure a smoother experience.</p>\n<p>If you’re ever unsure about your coverage or the claims process, working with a knowledgeable insurance professional such as <a href=\"contact.html\">Jiron Insurance Agency</a> can make all the difference.</p>\n<p>If you have an questions please don’t hesitate to call or text us at <a href=\"tel:7025220079\">(702)522-0079</a></p>"},{"slug":"home-insurance-in-nevada-what-homeowners-need-to-know-in-2026","title":"Home Insurance in Nevada: What Homeowners Need to Know in 2026","date":"January 2, 2026","ts":"2026-01-02T21:59:31+00:00","img":"assets/blog/img/home-insurance-in-nevada-what-homeowners-need-to-know-in-2026.png","cat":["Home","Hogar"],"excerpt":"Buying a home in Nevada is an exciting milestone, but protecting that investment with the right insurance policy is just as important. At Jiron Insurance Agency we are determined to help you","content":"<p>Buying a home in Nevada is an exciting milestone, but protecting that investment with the right insurance policy is just as important. At Jiron Insurance Agency we are determined to help you find the best coverage to suit your needs. In 2026, homeowners in Nevada face a shifting insurance landscape influenced by rising costs, evolving regulations, and natural-risk challenges. Here’s what every current or future homeowner should understand about <strong>home insurance in Nevada</strong> this year.</p>\n<h3><strong>1. How Much Does Homeowners Insurance Cost in Nevada?</strong></h3>\n<p>Nevada offers more affordable homeowners insurance compared to many other states, but costs can vary widely depending on coverage level, location, credit profile, and insurer.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>On average, homeowners in Nevada can expect to pay roughly <strong>$1,300–$1,400 per year</strong> for a standard policy — significantly lower than the national average. <a href=\"https://www.nerdwallet.com/insurance/homeowners/nevada-home-insurance?utm_source=chatgpt.com\">NerdWallet+1</a></li>\n<li>Specific average figures vary by data source, with some reporting around <strong>$1,305 annually</strong> and others closer to <strong>$1,444 a year</strong> for typical coverage amounts. <a href=\"https://www.nerdwallet.com/insurance/homeowners/nevada-home-insurance?utm_source=chatgpt.com\">NerdWallet+1</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Rates also differ by city, for example, <strong>Las Vegas and Henderson</strong> generally see premiums slightly higher than smaller towns. <a href=\"https://www.nerdwallet.com/insurance/homeowners/nevada-home-insurance?utm_source=chatgpt.com\">NerdWallet</a></p>\n<h3><strong>2. What Affects Your Premiums?</strong></h3>\n<p>Several factors play into how much you’ll pay for home insurance in Nevada:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Credit score:</strong> A strong credit profile can substantially lower premiums, while poor credit can dramatically increase costs. <a href=\"https://www.moneygeek.com/insurance/homeowners/average-cost-home-insurance-nevada/?utm_source=chatgpt.com\">MoneyGeek.com</a></li>\n<li><strong>Claims history:</strong> Multiple recent claims usually lead to higher rates. <a href=\"https://www.moneygeek.com/insurance/homeowners/average-cost-home-insurance-nevada/?utm_source=chatgpt.com\">MoneyGeek.com</a></li>\n<li><strong>Home construction and age:</strong> Newer homes with modern materials often cost less to insure. <a href=\"https://www.moneygeek.com/insurance/homeowners/average-cost-home-insurance-nevada/?utm_source=chatgpt.com\">MoneyGeek.com</a></li>\n<li><strong>Coverage amounts:</strong> Higher dwelling or liability limits increase premiums. <a href=\"https://www.moneygeek.com/insurance/homeowners/average-cost-home-insurance-nevada/?utm_source=chatgpt.com\">MoneyGeek.com</a></li>\n<li><strong>Location risk:</strong> Homes in areas prone to natural hazards typically cost more to insure.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>3. Natural Disasters &amp; Coverage Gaps to Watch Out For</strong></h3>\n<p>Nevada faces distinct risks homeowners must consider:</p>\n<p><strong>Wildfire Risk</strong></p>\n<p>While homeowners insurance traditionally included wildfire coverage, <strong>new state legislation effective January 1, 2026</strong> will allow insurers to <strong>exclude wildfire damage</strong> from standard policies under a temporary “sandbox” program. Homeowners may need to purchase standalone wildfire policies or add-ons to get this protection. <a href=\"https://nevadacurrent.com/2025/10/13/nevada-insurance-law-may-leave-consumers-exposed-to-wildfire/?utm_source=chatgpt.com\">Nevada Current+1</a></p>\n<p>This change has generated concern among experts who warn that thousands of homeowners, especially in wildfire-prone regions like the Reno-Tahoe area could be left financially unprotected if they don’t secure additional coverage. <a href=\"https://nevadacurrent.com/2025/10/13/nevada-insurance-law-may-leave-consumers-exposed-to-wildfire/?utm_source=chatgpt.com\">Nevada Current</a></p>\n<p><strong>Other Natural Perils</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Flooding:</strong> Standard homeowners insurance doesn’t cover flood damage. Separate flood insurance is a must if you’re in a flood zone. <a href=\"https://nextjs.insurify.com/homeowners-insurance/nevada/?utm_source=chatgpt.com\">Insurify</a></li>\n<li><strong>Earthquake:</strong> Earthquake coverage isn’t included and requires a separate policy. <a href=\"https://nextjs.insurify.com/homeowners-insurance/nevada/?utm_source=chatgpt.com\">Insurify</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Understanding what is and isn’t covered can save you from expensive surprises after a disaster.</p>\n<h3><strong>4. Tips for Getting the Best Coverage</strong></h3>\n<p>Here’s how Nevada homeowners can shop smart:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Compare multiple quotes:</strong> Rates vary widely from company to company.</li>\n<li><strong>Review policy details carefully:</strong> With changes on wildfire insurance, don’t assume coverage is included.</li>\n<li><strong>Ask about discounts:</strong> Bundling home and auto insurance, installing safety features, or maintaining a claims-free history can reduce costs. <a href=\"https://www.nerdwallet.com/insurance/homeowners/nevada-home-insurance?utm_source=chatgpt.com\">NerdWallet</a></li>\n<li><strong>Use state resources:</strong> The Nevada Division of Insurance has a consumer tool that helps identify which carriers are writing homeowners insurance in your ZIP code. <a href=\"https://business.nv.gov/News_Media/Press_Releases/2024/Insurance/Nevada_Division_of_Insurance_Announces_Consumer_Home_Insurance_Tool/?utm_source=chatgpt.com\">Nevada Business Portal</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>5. What’s Changing in 2025 and Beyond</strong></h3>\n<p>Nevada’s insurance market is in flux. Recent legislative moves aim to keep insurers participating in the state, even if that includes offering pared-down policies without wildfire coverage. <a href=\"https://nevadacurrent.com/2025/10/13/nevada-insurance-law-may-leave-consumers-exposed-to-wildfire/?utm_source=chatgpt.com\">Nevada Current</a></p>\n<p>Meanwhile, premiums have historically risen over the past several years reflecting broader national trends in construction costs, weather risks, and insurer underwriting adjustments. <a href=\"https://www.reviewjournal.com/business/housing/nevada-homeowners-insurance-up-over-20-in-past-6-years-report-says-3394978/?utm_source=chatgpt.com\">Las Vegas Review-Journal</a></p>\n<p>Staying informed and proactive will help Nevada homeowners navigate this changing landscape and ensure their most important asset stays protected.</p>\n<p>If you have further questions or need additional information do not hesitate to give us a call at <a href=\"tel:7025220079\">702-522-0079.</a></p>"},{"slug":"best-car-insurance-for-teen-drivers-in-nevada-arizona-new-mexico-2026-guide","title":"Best Car Insurance for Teen Drivers in Nevada, Arizona & New Mexico (2026 Guide)","date":"January 2, 2026","ts":"2026-01-02T21:56:56+00:00","img":"assets/blog/img/best-car-insurance-for-teen-drivers-in-nevada-arizona-new-mexico-2026-guide.png","cat":["Auto","Auto"],"excerpt":"Getting insurance for a teen driver can feel overwhelming both in terms of cost and coverage options. Teen drivers are statistically more likely to be involved in accidents than older driver","content":"<p>Getting insurance for a teen driver can feel overwhelming both in terms of cost and coverage options. Teen drivers are statistically more likely to be involved in accidents than older drivers, so premiums are often high nationwide. But with the right approach and company choice, you can find coverage that balances price, safety features, and discounts.</p>\n<p>Below, we break down what families in <strong>Nevada, Arizona, and New Mexico</strong> should know when choosing car insurance for their teen.</p>\n<h2><strong>Why Teen Auto Insurance Costs More</strong></h2>\n<p>Teen drivers are considered high-risk due to their limited driving experience. Insurers charge higher rates to account for this increased risk often <strong>two to four times</strong> what an older, experienced driver might pay.<a href=\"https://wallethub.com/answers/ci/best-car-insurance-for-young-drivers-in-nevada-1000188-2140796407/?utm_source=chatgpt.com\">WalletHub</a></p>\n<p>That makes choosing the right insurer and maximizing discounts essential to keeping premiums manageable.</p>\n<h2><strong>Top Coverage Considerations for Teen Drivers by State</strong></h2>\n<h3><strong>Nevada | Affordable &amp; Reliable Coverage</strong></h3>\n<p>In Nevada, families with teen drivers can often find reasonably priced coverage by focusing on policies that reward safe driving and academic achievement. Insurers in this state tend to offer competitive pricing for teens who maintain clean driving records and qualify for common discounts such as good-student or driver-training incentives.</p>\n<p>Policies that include safe-driving monitoring programs and accident-prevention features may also help lower overall premiums over time.</p>\n<p><strong>Tip:</strong> Adding a teen driver to an existing parent policy is usually far more cost-effective than purchasing a separate policy. This approach often results in significantly lower premiums while maintaining strong coverage.</p>\n<h3><strong>Arizona | Compare Multiple Quotes Carefully</strong></h3>\n<p>Teen auto insurance in Arizona can be more expensive than in neighboring states, making it especially important to shop around. Rates can vary widely depending on factors like the teen’s age, driving history, vehicle type, and location within the state.</p>\n<p>Some policies offer benefits such as accident forgiveness or usage-based programs that reward safe driving habits. Because pricing formulas differ, the most affordable option for one family may not be the same for another.</p>\n<p><strong>Arizona-Specific Insight:</strong> Always compare multiple quotes. Insurance costs for teen drivers can vary significantly based on how insurers evaluate age, driving experience, and risk.</p>\n<h3><strong>New Mexico | Budget-Friendly Teen Insurance Options</strong></h3>\n<p>New Mexico tends to offer more affordable teen auto insurance rates compared to many other states. Families can often find lower premiums by choosing basic liability coverage for safe vehicles and taking advantage of available discounts.</p>\n<p>Teen drivers who complete approved driver education programs or maintain good academic performance may qualify for reduced rates. Military-affiliated families and those with long-term, clean driving histories may also see additional savings opportunities.</p>\n<h2><strong>Ways to Lower Teens’ Insurance Costs</strong></h2>\n<p>Here are effective ways parents can keep rates down:</p>\n<p><strong>1. Use Discounts</strong></p>\n<p>Most carriers offer:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Good student discounts</strong> (B average or higher) which can significantly reduce premiums.</li>\n<li><strong>Driver education completion discounts</strong> for approved programs.</li>\n<li><strong>Safe driving/usage-based programs</strong> which offer rewards for good driving.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>2. Choose the Right Vehicle</strong></h3>\n<p>Insuring a safe, modestly powered vehicle usually costs less than insuring a large SUV or a sports car.</p>\n<h3><strong>3. Keep a Clean Driving Record</strong></h3>\n<p>Tickets and accidents dramatically increase premiums, especially for teens. Safe driving is financially as well as physically wise.</p>\n<h3><strong>4. Bundle Policies</strong></h3>\n<p>Combining auto coverage with other policies like home or renters insurance often earns lower overall rates with the same insurer.</p>\n<h2><strong>Final Tips for Parents</strong></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Shop for quotes every year.</strong> Teen insurance rates fluctuate. Comparing quotes yearly can save hundreds or even thousands.</li>\n<li><strong>Add the teen to a parent’s existing policy.</strong> Best first step for younger drivers.</li>\n<li><strong>Talk to an independent agent.</strong> They can provide multiple carrier options without extra charge.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Conclusion</strong></p>\n<p>Insuring a teen driver in Nevada, Arizona, or New Mexico doesn’t have to break the bank. With thoughtful comparison shopping, smart use of discounts, and making safety a priority, you can find coverage that fits both your budget and your peace of mind.</p>\n<p>If you have further questions or need additional information do not hesitate to give us a call at <a href=\"tel:7025220079\">702-522-0079.</a></p>"},{"slug":"9-factors-that-impact-your-auto-insurance-rates","title":"9 Factors that Impact Your Auto Insurance Rates","date":"December 22, 2025","ts":"2025-12-22T03:56:18+00:00","img":"assets/blog/img/9-factors-that-impact-your-auto-insurance-rates.png","cat":["Auto","Auto"],"excerpt":"Written By: Feliciano Jiron","content":"<p><strong>Written By: Feliciano Jiron</strong></p>\n<p>If you’ve ever looked at your insurance bill and wondered, <em>“How did they come up with this amount?”</em>—you’re not alone. Many people assume insurance premiums are arbitrary, but in reality, insurers rely on detailed data and risk analysis to calculate your rate. Every premium reflects how likely you are to file a claim and how costly that claim might be.</p>\n<p>Here are the key factors insurers use to determine your insurance premium and why each one matters.</p>\n<h3>Location</h3>\n<p>Where you live plays a major role in how much you pay for insurance. Urban areas typically have higher premiums due to increased traffic, higher accident rates, theft, and vandalism. Rural areas often come with lower rates because there’s generally less congestion and fewer claims.</p>\n<h3>Age</h3>\n<p>Age is a strong predictor of risk. Younger drivers, especially teens and those in their early 20s, tend to pay higher premiums because they statistically have less driving experience and higher accident rates. As drivers gain experience and maintain a clean record, premiums usually decrease.</p>\n<h3>Gender</h3>\n<p>For drivers under 25, gender can affect insurance costs. Statistically, young men are more likely to be involved in serious accidents than young women, which is why insurers often charge higher premiums for males in this age group. These differences tend to level out as drivers get older.</p>\n<h3>Credit Score</h3>\n<p>In many states, insurers use credit-based insurance scores to help predict risk. A higher credit score often leads to lower premiums because it’s associated with responsible financial behavior and fewer claims. A lower score may result in higher rates.</p>\n<h3>Driving Record</h3>\n<p>Your driving history is one of the most important factors in determining your premium. Tickets, accidents, and violations signal higher risk, while a clean driving record is often rewarded with lower rates and discounts.</p>\n<h3>Claims History</h3>\n<p>Filing multiple claims can increase your premium, even if you weren’t at fault. Insurers view frequent claims as a sign of higher future risk. Fewer claims over time can help keep your rates more affordable.</p>\n<h3>Vehicle Type</h3>\n<p>The make, model, and year of your vehicle matter more than you might think. Luxury vehicles, sports cars, and models with expensive repair costs typically have higher premiums. Vehicles with strong safety ratings and lower repair costs often come with more affordable rates.</p>\n<h3>Coverage Limits</h3>\n<p>Higher coverage limits provide more financial protection in the event of an accident, but they also increase your premium. Choosing the right balance between cost and protection is key to avoiding major out-of-pocket expenses later.</p>\n<h3>Deductibles</h3>\n<p>Your deductible is the amount you pay out of pocket before insurance coverage kicks in. A higher deductible usually lowers your monthly premium, but it also means you’ll pay more upfront if you file a claim. Lower deductibles increase premiums but reduce immediate costs after an accident.</p>\n<h3>The Bottom Line</h3>\n<p>Your insurance premium is a personalized calculation based on risk—not a random number. Understanding what affects your rate empowers you to make smarter decisions, whether that’s improving your credit, maintaining a clean driving record, or adjusting your coverage and deductible.</p>\n<p>Reviewing your policy regularly and working with a knowledgeable insurance professional can help ensure you’re getting the best value without sacrificing the protection you need.</p>\n<p>If you have further questions or need additional information do not hesitate to give us a call at <a href=\"tel:7025220079\">702-522-0079.</a></p>"},{"slug":"protecting-the-ones-you-love-with-life-insurance","title":"Protecting the Ones You Love with Life Insurance","date":"December 22, 2025","ts":"2025-12-22T03:46:56+00:00","img":"assets/blog/img/protecting-the-ones-you-love-with-life-insurance.png","cat":["Life","Vida"],"excerpt":"By: Feliciano Jiron","content":"<p><strong>By: Feliciano Jiron</strong></p>\n<p>Life insurance offers meaningful protection and peace of mind for the loved ones you leave behind. During an already difficult and emotional time, life insurance serves as both a financial and emotional lifeline, helping families navigate the uncertainty that follows a loss.</p>\n<p>From a financial standpoint, life insurance provides a reliable safety net that helps maintain stability when it is needed most. The funds can be used to cover essential expenses such as mortgage or rent payments, utilities, groceries, childcare, education costs, medical bills, and outstanding debts. This financial support allows your family to continue their day-to-day lives without the added burden of sudden financial strain, helping them preserve the lifestyle and security you worked hard to build.</p>\n<p>Emotionally, life insurance can ease stress and anxiety during a period when everything may feel overwhelming or chaotic. Knowing that bills will be paid and basic needs will be met allows your loved ones to focus on healing, supporting one another, and honoring your memory rather than worrying about finances. This peace of mind can make a significant difference in helping families regain their footing during a challenging transition.</p>\n<p>If you have questions about life insurance options or would like guidance in choosing the right coverage, don’t hesitate to give us a call at <a href=\"tel:7025220079\">(702)522-0079</a>. We are here to help you find a policy that best fits your family’s needs and provides lasting protection for the people who matter most.</p>"},{"slug":"tariffs-impact-on-auto-repair-costs-and-insurance-prices","title":"Tariffs Impact on Auto Repair Costs and Insurance Prices","date":"December 15, 2025","ts":"2025-12-15T06:23:54+00:00","img":"assets/blog/img/tariffs-impact-on-auto-repair-costs-and-insurance-prices.jpg","cat":["Auto","Auto"],"excerpt":"Written By: Feliciano Jiron","content":"<p><strong>Written By: Feliciano Jiron</strong></p>\n<p>With the increase of prices on Auto Parts becoming heavily impacted by the current Broad Tariffs that the United States has implemented along with a 25% levy on imported vehicles, as well as additional tariffs on Chinese steel, aluminum, and other items. These factors are truly raising the cost of vehicle components and mechanical parts across the U.S.</p>\n<p>According to <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/redir/redirect?url=http%3A%2F%2FInvestopedia%2Ecom&amp;urlhash=LHzv&amp;trk=public_post-text\">Investopedia.com</a> and <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/redir/redirect?url=http%3A%2F%2FKiplinger%2Ecom&amp;urlhash=EJjj&amp;trk=public_post-text\">Kiplinger.com</a> about 60% of U.S. replacement parts come from Mexico, Canada, and China, this significantly increases prices for both new components and maintenance parts. Auto repair shops are feeling the pressure and are already raising their prices to offset these costs. In the Detroit Free Press article from April 8, 2025, Skyler Chadwick from Cox Automotive warned that part prices may effectively double, especially for engines and electrical systems sourced and made overseas.</p>\n<p><strong>These rising repair costs do have a direct impact on Auto Insurance Prices:</strong></p>\n<p><em>- Rising claims and repair costs = higher premiums As the cost of repairing vehicles increases, insurance companies face increased claim payouts and ultimately pass these costs onto policyholders.</em></p>\n<p><em>- <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/redir/redirect?url=http%3A%2F%2FInsurify%2Ecom&amp;urlhash=EcUO&amp;trk=public_post-text\">Insurify.com</a> projects full-coverage auto insurance in the U.S. will reach around $2,759 in 2025, a 19% increase driven by tariffs—translating to roughly $324 more annually. Without tariffs, the expected increase was only about 5%.</em></p>\n<p><em>- On a state-by-state basis, consumers could see increases ranging from 12% to 24%, with some states like New York and Maryland seeing hikes of $533 to $568 due specifically to tariffs.</em></p>\n<p><em>- The American Property Casualty Insurance Association estimates tariffs could raise auto insurers’ claim costs by $7 billion to $24 billion annually in the next two years 2026 &amp; 2027. This financial pressure heightens the likelihood of widespread premium hikes.</em></p>\n<p>These changes and increases are now creating an environment where consumers are now shopping for the best price and the best coverage for their dollar. It is important for consumers who are exploring new auto insurance coverage to gather their information around their current rates, coverage types and any claims or cited driving violations as these will factor into new quoted rates. Remember that honesty is the best policy when approaching new insurance coverage, be upfront with the new companies quoting you to ensure that the initial quoted amount does not increase once your background data is run. This approach will allow you to benefit from better priced or improved auto coverage, lessening the stress of making this important decision.</p>"},{"slug":"understanding-auto-insurance-coverage-what-do-you-really-need","title":"Understanding Auto Insurance Coverage: What Do You Really Need?","date":"December 15, 2025","ts":"2025-12-15T06:16:39+00:00","img":"assets/blog/img/understanding-auto-insurance-coverage-what-do-you-really-need.png","cat":["Auto","Auto"],"excerpt":"Written By: Feliciano Jiron","content":"<p><strong>Written By: Feliciano Jiron</strong></p>\n<p>Many new auto insurance buyers have many questions, and the top of that list of questions is what type of insurance do I truly need to cover my vehicle. A quick rule of thumb is, if you are financing/making payments you will need full coverage per your purchase/lender agreements. If you own the vehicle and have paid it off, you have choices to maintain full coverage or purchase liability coverage/minimal requirements by law. Ultimately it is up to the consumer to determine their coverage needs as well as affordability considerations.</p>\n<h3><strong>Different car insurance options to consider?</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong><em>Liability Coverage</em></strong>: Covers Payment for injuries as well as property damage you cause to others in an accident.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong><em>Collision Coverage</em></strong>: Provides coverage for damage to your vehicle, from a collision whether you are at fault or not.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong><em>Comprehensive Coverage</em></strong>: Provides coverage when non-collision damages occur. Such as natural disasters, theft or vandalism.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong><em>Uninsured/Underinsured Motorist</em></strong>: Is protection, should you get into an accident with a driver who has no insurance or not enough coverage</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong><em>Personal Injury Protection</em></strong>: Provides medical expenses for you and your passengers, when an accident occurs.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you have further questions or need additional information do not hesitate to give us a call at <a href=\"tel:7025220079\">702-522-0079.</a></p>"},{"slug":"the-need-for-small-business-insurance-coverage","title":"The Need for Small Business Insurance Coverage","date":"December 7, 2025","ts":"2025-12-07T20:30:47+00:00","img":"assets/blog/img/the-need-for-small-business-insurance-coverage.png","cat":["Business","Negocio"],"excerpt":"Written By: Feliciano Jiron","content":"<p><strong>Written By: Feliciano Jiron</strong></p>\n<p>For small business owners, navigating the various risks that come with running a company can be a daunting task. From unexpected lawsuits to natural disasters, a single event can be catastrophic and even lead to the end of a business. This is where business insurance becomes an indispensable tool. It acts as a financial safety net, protecting your company's assets and providing crucial support in the face of unforeseen challenges. Policies like General Liability and Commercial Property insurance cover common risks such as customer injuries on your premises or damage to your building and equipment. Without proper coverage, a small business could be forced to pay for these costly events out of pocket, jeopardizing its stability and long-term viability.</p>\n<p>Beyond simply protecting your finances, having the right business insurance also instills a sense of credibility and professionalism. Many clients, partners, and landlords may require proof of insurance before entering into a contract with your business. This demonstrates a proactive approach to risk management and shows that you are prepared for potential issues. Additionally, certain types of insurance, such as workers' compensation, are often legally mandated for businesses with employees. By securing the appropriate coverage, you not only comply with the law but also provide essential protection for your staff in the event of a work-related injury or illness.</p>\n<p>Ultimately, business insurance offers peace of mind, allowing you to focus on growing your business with confidence, knowing that you are safeguarded against the unexpected.  If you have questions about the right business coverage.  Give the Jiron Insurance Agency a call at 702-522-0079, we are here to help you.</p>"},{"slug":"cost-of-insurance-and-driving-in-nevada","title":"Cost of Insurance and Driving in Nevada","date":"December 7, 2025","ts":"2025-12-07T20:25:04+00:00","img":"assets/blog/img/cost-of-insurance-and-driving-in-nevada.png","cat":["Auto","Auto"],"excerpt":"Written By: Feliciano Jiron","content":"<p><strong>Written By: Feliciano Jiron</strong></p>\n<p>As we have moved through 2025, we have seen market financial dynamics at play throughout the community and the Auto Insurance is no different. Many perspective clients are asking why the premium changes or what has changed to cause increased rates. Our goal is to give some perspective on what causes some of these impacts.</p>\n<p>Las Vegas, which is located in bustling Clark County, experiences around 1,114 traffic incidents per 100,000 residents, making its roads among Nevada’s most accident-prone. Fatal crashes across the state hover around 300 annually, with many occurring in the Las Vegas area with 162 Year to Date, based on data from the Nevada Office of Traffic Safety.</p>\n<p>On average, Las Vegas drivers face steep premiums. Compared to other Nevada cities, with locals shelling out around $2,712 annually, well above the state’s average of $2,143—and far above the national norm as reported by Car and Driver Magazine in 2025.</p>\n<p>Here’s a snapshot from <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/redir/redirect?url=http%3A%2F%2FAutoinsurance%2Ecom&amp;urlhash=ZmO_&amp;trk=public_post-text\">Autoinsurance.com</a>:</p>\n<p>•    State-level full coverage in Nevada averages $2,452/yr, with minimum coverage around $989/yr.    •    <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/redir/redirect?url=http%3A%2F%2FBankrate%2Ecom&amp;urlhash=wLcM&amp;trk=public_post-text\">Bankrate.com</a> (May 2025) pegs Nevada’s average at $1,067/yr for minimum and $3,575/yr for full coverage.</p>\n<p>Putting it all together: Why Vegas Drivers Pay More</p>\n<p>•    High accident rates</p>\n<p>•    Auto fatalities and crash counts across the Las Vegas Valley Communities</p>\n<p>•    Uninsured and out-of-state drivers, pushing insurers to hike rates for everyone</p>\n<p>•    Demographics: teen and young drivers pay higher premiums (Risk Demographic)</p>\n<p>•    Zip code risk factors, making location within Vegas a direct price impact as well</p>\n<p>•    Discounts offer some relief — however, understanding these discounts and how to get them is key. Even with bundling and clean records many individuals will still face periodic rate surges</p>\n<p>What do I do as an insurance consumer to watch my rates?</p>\n<p>Make sure you check your rates with your insurance company every 5-6 months. Also explore other insurance companies for quick quotes and know if your existing rates and coverage can be matched and the prices can be improved. A few minutes on a phone call can be worth the savings you will receive.</p>"}];
